tely and efficiently\nreplicates our analysis using $980\\times$ less computational time and\n$1330\\times$ fewer simulations than MCMC sampling using emcee. We find that\napproxposterior derives constraints with mean errors on the best fit values and\n$1\\sigma$ uncertainties of $0.61\\%$ and $5.5\\%$, respectively, relative to\nemcee.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Jun 2019 17:17:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Feb 2020 21:58:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-25"}
