ipoles $J_\\ell$ of the geopotential. In the latter case, the\nsystematic uncertainty due to the current formal errors $\\sigma_{J_\\ell}$ of a\nrecent global Earth's gravity field model are better than $1\\%$ for all the\npost-Newtonian effects considered, with a peak of $\\simeq 10^{-7}$ for the\nSchwarzschild-like shifts. [Abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Jun 2019 14:42:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-08"}
